  <title>Clutter.Actor::paint</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
def callback(actor, user_param1, ...)
</code></synopsis>
<p>The ::paint signal is emitted each time an actor is being painted.</p><p>Subclasses of <link xref="Clutter.Actor">Clutter.Actor</link> should override the class signal handler
and paint themselves in that function.</p><p>It is possible to connect a handler to the ::paint signal in order
to set up some custom aspect of a paint.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>actor :</p></td>
<td><p>instance of Clutter.Actor that is emitting the signal</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>user_param1 :</p></td>
<td><p>first user parameter (if any) specified with the connect() method</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>... :</p></td>
<td><p>additional user parameters (if any)</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 0.8</p>
